load_data module

Function to load the given data and return PyTorch dataset.

load_data.load_data(root: str, data: str, download: Optional[bool] = False, transform: Optional[Callable] = None) → Tuple[torch.utils.data.dataset.Dataset][source]

Load the specified dataset and create PyTorch datasets.

Parameters

  • root (str) – The root directory where the dataset is located. If the dataset does not exist locally, it will be downloaded here.

  • data (str) – The name of the dataset to load.

  • download (bool) – Boolean to indicate whether to download the dataset if it’s not already available locally.

  • transform (Optional[Callable]) – A PyTorch transform function that takes a PIL image and returns the transformed version. If None, it defaults to transform.ToTensor().

Returns

The training dataset. testds (torch.utils.data.Dataset]): The testing dataset.

Return type

trainds (torch.utils.data.Dataset)
